# muc-opcua feature configuration (Kconfig, consumed via kconfiglib).
#
# Generated from profiles/opcua-profile-manifest.yaml by
# scripts/profile_manifest/generate.py -- do not edit; regenerate with:
#   python3 scripts/profile_manifest/generate.py \
#       --manifest profiles/opcua-profile-manifest.yaml --outputs kconfig
#
# Symbol names are bare here; the build sets CONFIG_=MUC_OPCUA_ so the generated
# autoconf.h emits `#define MUC_OPCUA_<SYM> 1` (undefined for n -- #ifdef-safe) and
# .config/defconfig lines read `MUC_OPCUA_<SYM>=y`.  C sources keep their existing
# MUC_OPCUA_* macro names verbatim (no #ifdef-site changes).
#
# Model:
#   - `depends on`              = hard facet containment / build requirement.
#   - `default y if INTERN_*`   = internal cascade seeds defaults by lowest profile.
#   - Profile choice seeds defaults only; all facet/CU menus stay globally editable.
#   - Profiles are defconfigs (configs/<profile>.defconfig) selecting the choice.
#   - Unimplemented OPC items appear as Kconfig ``comment`` directives so they
#     are always visible in menuconfig but cannot be toggled (no config symbol).

mainmenu "muc-opcua configuration"

